27/09/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- UN Secretary General Kofi Annan and Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski have expressed hopes for a breakthrough in the name dispute between Greece and Macedonia.
During a meeting on the sidelines of the UN General Assembly, Annan and Crvenkovski jointly welcomed the recent announcements from Athens suggesting resolution of the dispute is now a government priority.
Meanwhile, Annan discussed Kosovo during a meeting Sunday (26 September) with Serbia-Montenegro's Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic.
He said Annan vowed to supply everything needed to protect Kosovo Serbs.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 27/09/04;
FoNet, B92 - 26/09/04)
